msgid "``tornado.tcpclient`` --- `.IOStream` connection factory"
msgstr ""

#: of tornado.tcpclient:1 tornado.tcpclient.TCPClient:1
msgid "A non-blocking TCP connection factory."
msgstr ""

#: of tornado.tcpclient.TCPClient:3
msgid "The ``io_loop`` argument (deprecated since version 4.1) has been removed."
msgstr ""

#: of tornado.tcpclient.TCPClient.connect:1
msgid "Connect to the given host and port."
msgstr ""

#: of tornado.tcpclient.TCPClient.connect:3
msgid ""
"Asynchronously returns an `.IOStream` (or `.SSLIOStream` if "
"``ssl_options`` is not None)."
msgstr ""

#: of tornado.tcpclient.TCPClient.connect:6
msgid ""
"Using the ``source_ip`` kwarg, one can specify the source IP address to "
"use when establishing the connection. In case the user needs to resolve "
"and use a specific interface, it has to be handled outside of Tornado as "
"this depends very much on the platform."
msgstr ""

#: of tornado.tcpclient.TCPClient.connect:12
msgid ""
"Raises `TimeoutError` if the input future does not complete before "
"``timeout``, which may be specified in any form allowed by "
"`.IOLoop.add_timeout` (i.e. a `datetime.timedelta` or an absolute time "
"relative to `.IOLoop.time`)"
msgstr ""

#: of tornado.tcpclient.TCPClient.connect:17
msgid ""
"Similarly, when the user requires a certain source port, it can be "
"specified using the ``source_port`` arg."
msgstr ""

#: of tornado.tcpclient.TCPClient.connect:20
msgid "Added the ``source_ip`` and ``source_port`` arguments."
msgstr ""

#: of tornado.tcpclient.TCPClient.connect:23
msgid "Added the ``timeout`` argument."
msgstr ""

